cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use signal-lag in your work, please cite it as below."
title: "signal-lag: patent-landscape-style foresight on AI-safety research"
abstract: >-
  signal-lag tracks topic velocity, citation dynamics, and sentiment across the
  AI research literature to surface where safety attention lags capability. It
  adds an LLM (Claude) analysis layer and a Foresight Gap synthesis that crosses
  research-trend signals with broader societal context to surface novel
  cross-domain risks, web-verified against current coverage. Runs as a live
  Streamlit dashboard on real arXiv, OpenAlex, Semantic Scholar, OpenReview, and
  lab-blog data, auto-refreshed weekly.
type: software
authors:
